<br><div class="container"><div class="horizontal-line"></div></div><h1>Introduction</h1><div class="container"><div class="horizontal-line"></div></div>
<p>Renowned Chinese educator and thinker Tao Xingzhi once said: &quot;Educating people is similar to growing flowers and trees. First, one must understand the characteristics of different flowers and trees, differentiate the situations, and provide fertilization, watering, and education accordingly. This is called tailoring education to individual differences.&quot; Our team&#39;s educational philosophy is inspired by the concept of &quot;tailoring education to individual differences.&quot; In the process of designing and conducting educational activities, we pay special attention to the differences in age groups and backgrounds. We conduct targeted educational activities suitable for understanding and practical application for different groups, including &quot;enlightenment education,&quot; &quot;extended education,&quot; &quot;advanced education,&quot; &quot;special education,&quot; and one-on-one interactive education. Additionally, we have created entertaining synthetic biology card games, mini-programs, and more for children and teenagers.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The following is the process for conducting our educational activities:</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig1-the-overall-process-of-education.png" width="400"/> </div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 1 The overall process of education</center></strong></p>
 
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<br><br><div class="container"><div class="horizontal-line"></div></div><h1>Enlightenment Education – Biological Paradise for Elementary School Students</h1><div class="container"><div class="horizontal-line"></div></div>
<p>A child&#39;s heart is like a clear and translucent pearl, innocent, pure, and beautiful. Children aged 6 to 12 are at the most innocent and lively age; they are filled with endless curiosity about everything in the natural world. As a team engaged in synthetic biology, we have closely approached the innocence and curiosity of primary school students. We have combined the background and needs of their learning life, using vivid and imaginative stories and fun games to paint a beautiful and joyful synthetic biology paradise for them.</p>
<p>The followings are the educational activities we have conducted for elementary school students:</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig2-educational-activities-for-elementary-school-students.png" width="800"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 2 Educational activities for elementary school students</center></strong></p>
 
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>CAU-China × Beijing Bozhi School</h2>
<h3>Target</h3>
<p>Children of migrant workers in grades 3 to 4 at Bozhi School.</p>
<h3>Activity Time</h3>
<p>May 26, 2023.</p>
<h3>Purpose</h3>
<p>“Good sons and daughters have ambitions, and those who have aspirations strive without regrets.” Many children at Bozhi School are the offspring of migrant workers. To harness the power of youth and support the revitalization of rural education, and to spark the children&#39;s interest in life sciences, our CAU-China team aims to introduce the world of synthetic biology in the simplest and most vivid language through fun and engaging educational courses and activities.</p>
<h3>Preparation: Why did we design the class in this way?</h3>
<p>The target audience for this educational activity is rural primary school students in grades 3 to 4. Although they have more direct contact with nature in their daily lives, they do not have a clear understanding of biology and biological sciences. Therefore, our team approaches the education from an enlightening perspective, using microorganisms as an example. We allow the children to understand synthetic biology based on their intuitive understanding of microorganisms.</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/haibao4.png" width="600"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 3 CAU-China &amp; Bozhi School Synthetic Biology Mini Classroom</center></strong></p>
 
<h3>Process</h3>
<p>The course is divided into two parts. The first part is “Microorganisms with Superpowers”, where we explained in simple terms that the secret to giving bacteria “superpowers” lies in synthetic biology. The children actively participated, raising many interesting questions such as “Can synthetic biology make people superheroes?” “Can synthetic biology make animals talk?” This demonstrated their curiosity and imagination about this emerging field.</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig3.png" width="600"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 4 The first part: Lecture on “Microorganisms with Superpowers”</center></strong></p>
 
<p>The second part is a game called “Synthetic Biology Fantasy Drawing”. We encouraged the children to unleash their imagination, using colorful pens to draw synthetic creatures on white paper based on their designs. They also had to give their creations a name and describe its function. The children came up with flying fish, color-changing cats, pollution-fighting carbon-cleaning bacteria, and more, showcasing their creativity and imagination.</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig5.png" width="600"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 5 The children are engaging in synthetic biology fantasy drawing</center></strong></p>
 
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig6.png" width="600"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 6 The “synthetic creatures” designed by the children</center></strong></p>
 
<h3>Feedback: How did our activities encouraged an open dialogue with audience?</h3>
<h4>For students: what have they learnt from our course?</h4>
<p>This educational activity has sparked the children&#39;s interest and curiosity in synthetic biology, broadening their horizons. In this land filled with hope and challenges, we see the gleam in the children&#39;s eyes – it&#39;s the thirst for knowledge and the dream for the future. With innocent hands, they express their gratitude to the volunteer teachers, feeling the love and care from afar with their pure hearts.</p>
<h4>For CAU-China: what did we received from this activity?</h4>
<p>Volunteering at Bozhi School feels like stepping back into our own elementary school days, experiencing the innocence on the children&#39;s faces and their vibrant energy. The greetings of “Hello, teacher” and “Teacher, you&#39;ve worked hard” are deeply engraved in our hearts. We shared knowledge about synthetic biology with the children, guiding them to imagine and design fantastic creatures. In their lively drawings, we saw their thirst for knowledge and their passionate creativity. Volunteering isn&#39;t just teaching; it&#39;s also spreading love to the world.</p>
<p>The enthusiasm and creativity of the children inspire us to imagine boldly and experiment bravely, exploring more interesting and enriching ideas for our own project.</p>
<h4>For the teachers at Bozhi School: what do you want to say to CAU-China?</h4>
<p>The teachers from Bozhi School expressed high praise for this activity and thanked CAU-China for bringing an unforgettable scientific journey to the children.</p>
