<h2>CAU-China × Chunshuguan Community</h2>
<h3>Target</h3>
<p>Elementary school students from grades 1 to 6 in the urban community.</p>
<h3>Activity Time</h3>
<p>July 20, 2023.</p>
<h3>Purpose</h3>
<p>During the summer vacation, many elementary school students gather in the urban community. Together with the “Brilliant Science” summer social practice team from China Agricultural University, utilized the resources at the Chunshuguan Community Activity Station in Beijing&#39;s Xicheng District, we hope to bring rich and interesting knowledge to the urban children through our distinctive introductory courses in synthetic biology. We aimed to help them understand the diverse and colorful world of biology.</p>
<h3>Preparation：Why did we design the class in this way?</h3>
<p>The target audience for this educational activity is elementary school students in grades 1 to 6 in urban areas. Compared to students from rural schools, they have a basic understanding of life and biology. Therefore, we incorporated some additional content in our curriculum design, such as the relationship between gut microbiota and humans, and an introduction to central dogma, among others. Furthermore, to showcase the wonders of synthetic biology, we explained our project in a simple and understandable way. While enhancing the accessibility and fun of the courses, we focused on giving methodical and patient guidance, aiming to encourage children to think deeply about topics such as the relationship between biology and humans, the underlying design of living organisms, and the contributions of synthetic biology to the world.</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/haibao5.png" width="400"/> </div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 7 CAU-China &amp; &quot;Brilliant Science&quot; Team Science Education Activities</center></strong></p>
<h3>Process</h3>
<p>With the collaboration of the &quot;Brilliant Science&quot; team members, we conducted two parts of the activity: a fun classroom session titled &quot;From Microorganisms to Synthetic Biology&quot; and a &quot;Knowledge Blind Box Quiz&quot;.</p>
<p>In the first part, CAU-China member Liu Xiangjun introduced various microorganisms such as bacteria and actinomycetes by incorporating scenes from the children&#39;s daily lives. Using audiovisual methods, he explained the relationship between gut microbiota and human health. He used the analogy of a “car production line” to explain “protein synthesis” and introduced the central dogma. Finally, he used the example of a designer (gene) modifying a car (organism) to explain the concept of synthetic biology. During the class, the students listened attentively and actively participated in interactive sessions, gaining a lot from the classroom where fun and knowledge coexisted.</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig8.png" width="600"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 8 The classroom session on &quot;From Microorganisms to Synthetic Biology&quot;</center></strong></p>
 
<p>In the second part, we organized a &quot;Knowledge Blind Box Quiz&quot; game. We created interesting biology trivia questions and knowledge points from the lesson into small cards, which were then placed inside blind boxes. The children picked a card and participated in rapid answering and discussions. The atmosphere was lively, and the children showed strong interest in questions like &quot;Why can we smell the earthy scent after the rain?&quot; and &quot;How does yeast produce artemisinin?&quot; This reflected their curiosity about the biological world and synthetic biology.</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig9.png" width="600"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 9 The &quot;Knowledge Blind Box Grand Quiz&quot; segment</center></strong></p>
 
<h3>Feedback: How did our activities encouraged an open dialogue with audience?</h3>
<h4>For students: what have they learnt from our course?</h4>
<p>In this activity, the children showed strong interest in new knowledge such as the central dogma and synthetic biology. Additionally, we noticed their curiosity about scientific explanations for everyday phenomena they often encounter. They were eager to learn scientific principles that contradicted their previous understanding. During the class, the children actively participated, collaborated, and solved various interesting biology-related questions. This not only broadened their horizons but also enriched their knowledge.</p>
<h4>For CAU-China: what did we received from this activity?</h4>
<p>In this educational activity, as young teachers, we delivered engaging lessons to our classmates, establishing friendly interactions and friendships with the children. At the same time, we gained valuable experience and learned how to popularize our field of study to society, enabling more people to understand biology, love biology, and apply biological knowledge!</p>
<p>Additionally, the reactions and attitudes of the children taught us a lot. We have started to pay more attention to details and critically think about abnormal experimental results while advancing our project. We aim to summarize new patterns and insights from these experiences.</p>
<h4>For the staff at Chunshuguan Community: what do you want to say to CAU-China?</h4>
<p>&quot;Your courses and activities not only taught valuable knowledge to the children in our community but also provided them with an unforgettable experience. More importantly, your presence showcased the dedication and social responsibility of university students. We were deeply moved by your enthusiasm and efforts, and you have set a great example for the children in our community.&quot;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>CAU-China &amp; BIT-China × Synthetic Biology Innovation and Practice Camp</h2>
<h3>Target</h3>
<p>Elementary school students from the Synthetic Biology Innovation and Practice Camp.</p>
<h3>Activity Time</h3>
<p>July 12, 2023.</p>
<h3>Purpose</h3>
<p>During the summer vacation, Beijing Institute of Technology (BIT) organized an almighty youth summer camp for elementary school students. Our team received an invitation from the BIT-China team to join their Synthetic Biology Innovation and Practice Camp. Together, we prepared and organized a microbial painting activity. The purpose of this activity was to allow children to experience the charm of synthetic biology through hands-on participation.</p>
<h3>Preparation：Why did we design the class in this way?</h3>
<p>During the Synthetic Biology Innovation and Practice Camp at Beijing Institute of Technology, the children had received a comprehensive and systematic biology education for three days. They learned about topics such as cell structure, DNA, etc., which gave them a deeper understanding of biology. To provide the children with a more hands-on experience of synthetic biology, we expressed fluorescent proteins of green, pink, and purple colors in bacteria. The aim was for the children to feel the charm of synthetic biology during the process of artistic creation.</p>
<h3>Process</h3>
<p>The event was organized by BIT-China, with the volunteer co-organization by the CAU-China team. During the event, Teacher Yu from Beijing Institute of Technology introduced the principles and steps of microbial painting to the children. The children were curious and eager to try it out. With our guidance, they opened the culture mediums and used toothpicks to dab different bacterial solutions, starting their artwork on the culture mediums.</p>
<p>Throughout the painting process, we engaged in deep conversations with the children, answering questions like &quot;Why do bacteria glow?&quot; and &quot;How long does it take for bacteria to grow and glow after cultivation?&quot; The atmosphere was lively, and the children expressed their love for the activity through laughter and joy.</p>
<p>For more information, you can browse the wiki of BIT-China: <a href="https://2023.igem.wiki/bit-china/education#title_4">https://2023.igem.wiki/bit-china/education#title_4</a></p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig10.png" width="600"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 10 The microbial painting activity co-organized with BIT-China</center></strong></p>
 
<h3>Feedback: How did our activities encouraged an open dialogue with audience?</h3>
<h4>For students: what have they learnt from our course?</h4>
<p>The time spent on the fun microbial painting activity was joyful yet brief. After showcasing their artistic talents, the children all looked back with endless delight and eagerly anticipated more engaging activities in synthetic biology. They were deeply fascinated by the magic of &quot;glowing bacteria&quot; and synthetic biology.</p>
<h4>For CAU-China: what did we received from this activity?</h4>
<p>This activity marked the first time we shared laboratory techniques and procedures with children who shared our interest in this field. Explaining the theories and procedures of these experiments was a unique and unforgettable experience for us.</p>
<p>Simultaneously, the children&#39;s inquisitive learning attitude deeply inspired us. It encouraged us to delve deeper into technical principles and learn more thoroughly. A rigorous, earnest, and excellence-seeking attitude in scientific research is always the noblest quality for a researcher!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<br><br><div class="container"><div class="horizontal-line"></div></div><h1>Extended Education - Introduction to Biology for Middle School Students</h1><div class="container"><div class="horizontal-line"></div></div>
<p>Adolescent are like blooming flowers, representing the future of the world. Adolescents between the ages of 12 and 18 are in the stage of learning and exploring the unknown. They actively seek out new things and question concepts that contradict their existing knowledge. As a team engaged in synthetic biology, we have closely approached the curiosity of teenagers. Building upon their existing knowledge of biology, we delved deeper into life sciences, life logic, and introduced them to the new world of synthetic biology.</p>
<p>The followings are the educational activities we have conducted for the middle school students:</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig11.png" width="800"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 11 Educational activities for middle school students</center></strong></p>
 
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Adaptive Science Education Course</h2>
<h3>Target</h3>
<p>Middle school students from Daxing District, Dandelion Middle School, Beijing, the &quot;Getting Closer to Nature&quot; camp.</p>
<h3>Activity Time</h3>
<p>July 14, 2023.</p>
<h3>Purpose</h3>
<p>During the summer vacation, Dandelion Middle School organized the 18th annual summer camp, featuring both a growth camp and themed camps. Our CAU-China team volunteered for the &quot;Getting Closer to Nature&quot; themed camp. Through this opportunity, we aimed to engage in discussions with middle school students and explore life sciences and synthetic biology together. Collaborating with the &quot;Shining Flame&quot; social practice team from China Agricultural University, we jointly conducted science education sessions and fun games for teenagers participating in the &quot;Getting Closer to Nature&quot; themed camp.</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/haibao3.png" width="400"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 12 CAU-China &amp; &quot;Shining Flame&quot; Team science education activities</center></strong></p>
 
<h3>Preparation：Why did we design the class in this way?</h3>
<p>As middle school students, participants of the &quot;Getting Closer to Nature&quot; themed camp had already learned basic biology such as cell biology and physiology. Therefore, in the course design, we focused on expanding and extending their knowledge based on the review. For example, we guided the students to review the basic knowledge of the cell nucleus and then expanded to chromosomes and DNA, introducing the central dogma and basic principles of genetics.</p>
<p>Teenagers possess a strong curiosity and thirst for knowledge in unknown fields, and synthetic biology perfectly satisfies their curiosity. We introduced the principles of using synthetic biology to modify organisms and inspired their biological logic, imagination and creativity through games such as pathway assembly and brainstorming sessions.</p>
<h3>Process</h3>
<p>This course is divided into two parts. In the first part, our team member Liu Xiangjun introduced the basic knowledge of microbiology and the central dogma.By making comparisons with traditional biology, he elaborately explained the development history and principles of synthetic biology, providing the students with a basic understanding of synthetic biology. Following that, team member Yu Jingwen led the students in an assembly pathway game. After explaining the functions and applications of various components such as promoters and terminators in vivid and simple language, the students had hands-on experience in designing genetic pathways. Members of CAU-China helped the students solve various problems they encountered. Through the game, the students practically understood the assembly sequence of various components and experienced the fun of synthetic biology.</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig13.png" width="600"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 13 Introduction to synthetic biology and pathway assembly game</center></strong></p>
 
<p>In the second part, team member Xu Linjie further introduced the iGEM competition and outstanding synthetic biology projects from previous years. He elaborated on CAU-China&#39;s project &quot;My Si-lium&quot; in 2023, sharing the project&#39;s design concepts with the students. Following this, we led the students in a brainstorming session, guiding them to think along the lines of synthetic biology problem-solving approaches and design their own small synthetic biology projects. With the assistance of CAU-China members, the students applied the knowledge they had just learned, unleashed their creativity, and engaged in intense discussions.</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig14.png" width="600"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 14 Introduction to iGEM project and brainstorming game</center></strong></p>
 
<h3>Feedback: How did our activities encouraged an open dialogue with audience?</h3>
<h4>For students: what have they learnt from our course?</h4>
<p>This series of adaptive courses and activities provided the students with a fresh perspective on biology. They gained insights into the principles of synthetic biology and the incredibly cool iGEM projects, especially our own project. The students showed a keen interest in our project and had a great time exploring it within the span of a day.</p>
<center>
<iframe title="CAU-China:  Dandelion Middle School Education Activity Feedback (2023) [Chinese]" width="560" height="315" src="https://video.igem.org/videos/embed/16e0a764-7dcc-4403-8877-345669b5d7e4" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" sandbox="allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-popups"></iframe></center>
<h4>For CAU-China: what did we received from this activity?</h4>
<p>In the process of designing the course, we aimed to present the principles of synthetic biology in a vivid and in-depth manner. We also wanted to share iGEM and our project with everyone. We utilized numerous examples and illustrations and we achieved this goal.</p>
 
<div align="center"> <img src="https://static.igem.wiki/teams/4614/wiki/education/fig15.png" width="600"/> </div>
<p> <strong><center>Fig. 15 Presentation slides on synthetic biology and our project</center></strong></p>
 
<p>Students have given our project high praise, considering the idea to be excellent. They are looking forward to seeing our material applied in real-life situations in the future. Their feedback undoubtedly inspires our team greatly. We are determined to improve the project, making it even more practical (for example, by adjusting the filamentation to increase the material&#39;s porosity and enhance its sound absorption capabilities).</p>
