<p>Children with autism often have a lower willingness to interact socially with others, and our picture book activity might be the key to unlocking their hearts. During the process of coloring and drawing, some children immersed themselves in the fascinating world of synthetic biology, while others bravely sharing happiness with everyone. We believe that this activity not only facilitated communication and interaction among the children but also added beautiful colors to their inner world.</p>
<h4>For CAU-China: what did we received from this activity?</h4>
<p>The picture book sharing activity brought us closer to a special group, making us truly realize that our project and synthetic biology can bring joy to these children and nurture their hearts. At the same time, we realized that our inclusivity and care are always needed by the world.</p>
